data.enText: able to think of new and interesting ideas

data.chText: 她的头脑非常善于创新。
data.enText: She has a highly inventive mind.

tr: (used of persons or artifacts) marked by independence and creativity in thought or action
example: the invention of the knitting frame by another ingenious English clergyman"- Lewis Mumfor
had an inventive turn of mind

value.def: An inventive person is good at inventing things or has clever and original ideas.

example.tran: 斯特罗曼永远求新的舞蹈设计

example.ex: It inspired me to be more inventive with my own cooking.
example.tran: 它激发我在自己烹饪时更富创造性。

value.tran: 善于发明的;有创造才能的

example.ex: He has surprised us before with his inventiveness.
example.tran: 以前他的发明才能曾令我们惊讶。
